text: Martin Chlumecký (born 11 January 1997) is a Czech football player who currently plays for FK Dukla Prague. ==Career== He scored three own goals in his first five Czech First League matches for Dukla, scoring the only goal of Dukla's 1–0 home defeat to Bohemians 1905, followed by both opposition goals in the 2–1 home defeat against 1. FC Slovácko. He joined Vysočina Jihlava on a half-season loan during the winter break of the 2018–19 season. ==References== ==External links== * * * Martin Chlumecký at Footballdatabase Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:Czech footballers Category:Association football defenders Category:FC Slovan Liberec players Category:FK Varnsdorf players Category:FK Dukla Prague players Category:FC Vysočina Jihlava players Category:Czech First League players Category:Czech National Football League players
